rComments: A great prof! She gives back feedback and always makes herself available if students have questions. Go to class and put in the effort there is no reason why you can't get an A.
Excellent professor. Provides multiple perspectives on the Census and aspires to teach critical thinking. Very open to helping students and fostering an environment of contentious discussion.
Amazing course, not difficult prof at all.
great at explaining concepts. A little stand off-ish but she is nice. I found the work although it didn't seem hard was marked hard, and the marking was a bit ambiguous.

She is honestly one of the best prof's I even had her as my TA and she is very open to helping us with her course and other courses in terms of studying. Very encouraging and her course is something worth taking because she is teaching it :)

Professor Kmiec doesn' try to trick you. She makes her expectations really clear and goes above and beyond to proof read your assignments before you hand it in. She is one of the few professors at U of T that actually want her students to succeed. Her lectures are actually fascinating and her slides are helpful for exam prep.

Prof. Kmiec was really great. She's enthusiastic and clearly has an interest in the material she teaches. The assignments were not difficult and the tutorials were very helpful. She brought in guest speakers where necessary and had a lot of critical discussion take place during class time which always kept things interesting. Highly recommend!
